article.headline: Georgia Southern 61, Mercer 59
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- Donte Gennie's jumper with 14 seconds remaining lifted Georgia Southern to a 61-59 victory over Mercer Monday night. Gennie scored after Louis Graham grabbed a rebound on a missed jumper by Mercer's James Florence on the other end. Florence missed a 3-point try at the buzzer. Graham finished with 18 points and 17 rebounds for Georgia Southern (3-2), while Gennie scored 16. Florence had 19 points, but was 0-3 from 3-point range. Aaron Shaddean added 12 points for the Bears (1-3). After trailing as much as 25-15 at 6:37 of the first half, the Eagles took a 27-29 lead with 44 seconds remaining, but Florence scored after a Gennie turnover to make it 29-29 at intermission. Georgia Southern led most of the second half, but never by more than six, 39-33 with 16:35 to play. Mercer trailed 59-56 before Ross Alacqua's 3-pointer tied it with 58 seconds left.
